  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rebuilding St. Croix, USVI</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The St. Croix Long Term Recovery Group (LTRG) was formed after the impact of two back-to-back Cat 5 hurricanes: Irma and Maria. It is also mobilizing post-Dorian. The LTRG is a collective of individuals, businesses, non-profit and faith-based institutions whose goal it is to unite recovery resources with community needs.  The LTRG ensures that the most vulnerable among Virgin Islanders can safely return to their homes as quickly as possible and be wholly recovered from ongoing impacts of storms.</narrative>
  </description>
